Business Brief -- Toll Brothers Inc.:
   Building Concern Reports
   1st-Period Net Rose Sharply
"We are encouraged by the general improvement in demand we
have experienced in our markets," said Robert I. Toll,
chairman and chief executive officer. The company builds and
finances single-family houses, townhouses and condominiums in
the Northeast.
   Toll Brothers said the value of new sales contracts
reached the highest level for any first quarter in its
history, rising to $56.9 million from $25 million in the
yearearlier period. The sales value of the backlog of homes
under contract as of Jan. 31 reached a record $130.6 million
vs. $59.6 million in 1990.